        <button class="faq-tab active" data-tab="legal" type="button">Legal &amp; RDC <span class="faq-tab-count">4</span></button>
        <button class="faq-tab" data-tab="start" type="button">Getting Started <span class="faq-tab-count">3</span></button>
        <button class="faq-tab" data-tab="pricing" type="button">Pricing &amp; Data <span class="faq-tab-count">5</span></button>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-panel active" data-panel="legal">
        <div class="faq-list">

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Is a Snagify report actually accepted by the Dubai Rental Dispute Center (RDC)?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Every Snagify report includes the evidence the RDC looks for: timestamped entries, dual signatures, photos with metadata, and a SHA-256 hash proving the file hasn't been altered after signature. You submit the PDF as-is. No notarisation, no reformatting. Your agency name, logo, and RERA number appear on every page.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">What happens if the tenant refuses to sign?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>You document the refusal inside the report. A dedicated field logs the refusal with timestamp and optional reason. The report stays legally valid. A documented refusal is strong evidence that your agency followed due process, which protects both you and your landlord client if the case reaches the RDC.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Is Snagify certified by RERA?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>RERA regulates brokers, not software. Snagify follows RERA's inspection guidelines (room by room breakdown, dual signatures, photo documentation) and our report format matches the criteria RERA applies when reviewing disputes. Your RERA broker number appears on every report.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Can I use a Snagify report as evidence in court?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. The RDC and Dubai civil courts accept digitally signed documents with verifiable timestamps. The SHA-256 hash on every PDF is cryptographic proof that the file hasn't been tampered with. A lawyer can verify it in under a minute if challenged.</p></div></div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-panel" data-panel="start">
        <div class="faq-list">

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Do I need to train my inspectors?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Most inspectors are productive on their first real inspection. The flow is guided step by step: add property, walk room by room, photograph, tag, sign. Every inspector follows the same process, so reports stay consistent across your whole agency.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">How long does an inspection actually take?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Around 20 minutes for a 1 bedroom apartment. 30 to 40 minutes for a villa with 4 or more rooms. First time setup adds 2 to 3 minutes for the address and rooms. Once a property is in the system, every check-out reuses the check-in template, which makes it much faster.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Does it work offline on-site?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Snagify is a PWA, so it installs on your phone and runs offline once loaded. Photos and AI tagging queue locally and sync when you're back online. You can start in a basement with no signal, finish on the rooftop, and nothing is lost.</p></div></div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-panel" data-panel="pricing">
        <div class="faq-list">

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Can I bill my client for inspections?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, and most agencies already do. Move-in and move-out fees are standard practice in Dubai property management. Snagify gives you a branded, RDC-valid report that justifies the fee and positions inspection as a premium service. Typical rates range from 150 to 300 AED per inspection. The ROI calculator above shows what this looks like at your volume.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item" id="faq-credits-pro">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">How do credits work on Pro plans? Can my team share them?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Each inspection, check-in or check-out, uses 1 credit. Your plan's credits refresh monthly, and unused credits roll over while your subscription is active. All inspectors in your team share one credit pool, so no one runs out while another has extras. Extra credits beyond your plan cost 16 to 28 AED each depending on your tier.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Can I cancel my subscription anytime?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Monthly plans cancel in one click. No fees, no questions. You keep access until the end of your billing period, and every report you've ever generated stays accessible forever.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Where is my data stored? Is it secure?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Reports, photos, and signatures are stored on encrypted servers. Photos are analysed by AI and then discarded. Only the final report is retained. SHA-256 hashes detect any tampering. Your data is never sold, shared, or used for AI training.</p></div></div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" type="button">Do I keep my reports if I stop my subscription?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Forever. Every PDF you've generated stays in your account, downloadable anytime. If you cancel, you keep read-only access to all past reports. You just can't create new ones until you reactivate.</p></div></div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

